title: For Sale:  WWII M1911A1 C/M Transfer
postcontent:
Up for sale is a very rare and sought after Colt "Commerical to Military Transfer" M1911A1 WWII Pistol in "Parts/Shooter" grade. Only about 6,500 of these made. Slide and frame are both Commerical/Military trasnfer serial range numbers. But since they do not match is why I am only asking $2300. When in serial matching, they fetch $6,000 - $9,000. History: When Colt received the WWII contract a sudden need for pistols was needed. So Colt pulled what they had produced from shelfs for their commerical line for the Military contract. These commerical pistols had their schwartz safeys removed, commercial serials peened over and military serials crudley stamped over, other military markings added then parkerized. As seen on the slide in front portion, the darker color. This is from the re-finishing from Colt to "Militarizing" the pistols in parkized from the blued. In the time these pistols were flamed hardened in the front portion. This flame hardening becomes very visible when its re-finished. As it was from Colt to get them converted for the Milirarty contract.
Link of one with serial match sold recently:
http://www.pre98.com/shop/gone-but-not-forgotten/colt-1911a1-1943-commercial-military-very-rare-sharp/I do not have the story as to why of the million or so WWII M1911A1 pistols that were produced. That this pistol somehow has both seriallized parts from the 6,500 C/M pistols serial range (Commerical/Military). Only 453 seperate the two serials. This pistol may have been mixed matched in a arensal very early in its life or by colt. I can not say. Both the wear and aging is matching to both frame and slide so these two have been together for a very long while.If you have any other quoestions, please feel free to ask.If you want to text or talk, please email phone number.Cash only, and local face to face transactions only. I only do my transactions at local police depts. (Which is enocouraged by most depts.)
